│ THOUGHT: The debug output shows that the `isMoreProfitable` function is comparing vectorization factors with    │
│ different widths and costs. The scalable vectorization factor (`vscale x 2`) has a higher cost than the scalar  │
│ factor (`1`), which leads to the scalar factor being selected as `BestFactor`. This mismatch with the legacy    │
│ cost model's `LegacyVF.Width` (`vscale x 2`) is causing the assertion failure.                                  │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ To address this, I will modify the `isMoreProfitable` function to ensure that scalable vectorization factors    │
│ are not unfairly penalized due to their higher costs. Specifically, I will adjust the comparison logic to favor │
│ scalable factors when their costs are close to those of fixed-width factors.                                    │
